The paper deals with graph drawing and optimization, which are central topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem of crossing minimization is a classic problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization (cs.DS, cs.DM). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.GT). Finally, the paper presents a polynomial-time solution for a specific case, which falls under the category of algorithm design and analysis (cs.CC).
